{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-05700/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-05700"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:57:00"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["medium shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, handheld, pan, tilt"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["dirty single"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A man speaks to a woman in another room as he puts on his bow tie."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05700/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-05700","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05700/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-05700"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05700/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05700/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05700/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05700/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05700/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05700/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05700/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05700/canvas/1/9a75d8f0-5c68-4a1d-b941-cc9c26c73bf2","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T14:54:35.000Z","creator":"Tallulah Stallvik","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Reynolds says that he’s “so hungry.” On a literal level, he’s ready for breakfast. More figuratively, he’s ready to get back to work and to commit to his art after a period of depression. Alma seems to recognize this shift, as her own face moves from joy when watching him in the kitchen to a slight disappointment when he joins her at the table and she sees his vigor has returned. These swings in attitude define their relationship in which Alma provides both the poison that will lay him flat and the tender care that will nurse him back to health.</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05700/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:1011.0055905963303,199.54558486238537,297.4670298165137,397.67201834862396"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05700/canvas/1/f5adb1fb-6976-48fc-b8c4-f60c57be6094","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T14:54:52.134Z","creator":"Tallulah Stallvik","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>The bowtie Reynolds wears appears to be the same one he wore during the first breakfast, in the scene with his previous girlfriend Johanna. The contrast between the two scenes is clearly drawn—while there he was calm, emotionless, here he seems invigorated and full of energy. Alma has reignited his passion. However, Reynolds has not yet reciprocated Alma’s admission of love, an issue she does not press. Her attempts to deepen their relationship, like Johanna’s, are (at least for now) ignored.</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05700/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:940.3189506880735,619.9369266055047,362.928612385321,230.625"}}}]}]}]}